30/07/2003
THESSALONIKI, Greece -- At a meeting of the UN Online Network in Public Administration and Finance in Thessaloniki on Tuesday (29 July), Minister of Macedonia-Thrace Haris Kastanidis proposed the creation of a Balkan Ombudsman. According to Kastanidis, the institution would follow the example of the European Ombudsman and would help the region solve problems related to bureaucracy and mismanagement, while encouraging co-operation among neighbouring countries. (MPA - 29/07/03)
